  <abstract>Bear Spring Furnace, four miles east of Dover at Bear Spring. Detail of the base and hearth area located on the north side.</abstract>
  <abstract>The original charcoal cold-blast furnace was built in 1830 by Woods, Yeatman &amp; Co. as part of Cumberland Iron Works. By 1850, the furnace produced over 2000 tons of metal. In 1862, the stack was destroyed by Union troops, and it was reconstructed in 1873.</abstract>
